spanGrp.span: M kom estee pekaga sr-g ska
He had a lot of apples planted;
Je r jie-wa w esteee pekaga w mansana/ je t mansana tka t' jeska
so he climbed up a tree to bring them down.
er jie mnu (m) jula jrga mansana bts
When he was up on the apple trees branch, a child came by on his bike and took a basket full of ripe apples.
er jie ka (_) ka/ ka/ jie katerga m m estee mansana jula ska er yaba daj-te bisikleta inga (_) (_) jaba mntse je (_) je (_) jaba jaba mntse shlita estee mansana eb
As he was going away uh a girl was coming;
er m dam kom ra estee peyaba busi daj
so he turned to see her and thus did not see the stone before him so his bike crashed against it;
er je wch-m s er ka jie-wa jak sun w ts er je mnu-te n (_) bisikleta mnu t-n esteee jak m
So there were other children who came to help him pick up the apples.
Jeke/ je batamra estee m yabla datse (hm) t kim' estee mansana shtga
They put the apples back in the basket and then they left.
je ji-w-ite jaba jrga er etabagl yaba yaba mnu-m-n
They got to where the hat was lying and one of them shouted at him and ran toward him to hand it over to him.
M yaba mnu-m m sombrero jatan'-w je ju' yaba an' tsaga er je mnu tu-l ju'
Then the child paid him back with three apples;
er m estee yaba t patu' estee (_) mansana m'-ite m-l
one for each because there were three kids.
Je r e-gla e-gla porke jie-wa r m-l
Next the man came down and picked up the apples
er m estee pekaga jk jaw-te t t mansana sht
but noticed that a basket was missing;
kai mans/ (_) era jaba shen e-gla
only one of them was full; the other one wasnt.
(_) E-gla ka r shi e-gla b r shi--ra
So he realized that the apples were missing.
er pekaga t s'-ra kai mansana jue-n
So the children threw the hat at him and went back.
er yabla (m) t sombrero ju' er jie-wa beteu-lo-te
